TABLES

Tables are used to represent real life table data.
Table Header -> main content(e.g. Name, Roll No.)
To represent data there are three types of Tags:
<tr> used to display table row.
<td> used to display table data.
<th> used to display table header.

**SEMANTIC**

<thread> to wrap table header
<tbody> to wrap table body
<tfoot> to wrap table footer

**Colspan and Rowspan Attributes**

<th Colspan="2"> price </th>
<th rowspan="2"> Item </th>

**Forms**
<forms>
    content
</forms>

< form action="/action.php" >
< form action="/action" >

**Form Elements**
Input
• used to create multiple form controls
• there are multiple types of inputs that can be created using type attribute

type attribute
<input>
<input type= "text">
<input type= "password">
<input type= "number">
‹input type= "time">
<input type="color">

**Placeholder Attribute**         (Sub heading of Form)

<input type="text" placeholder="Enter Name">

*LABEL*
• Label element represents a caption for an item in a user interface
<label >
Enter your username :
<input type="text" placeholder= "username">
</label>

Label Classical Approach
<label for="username"> Enter your username : </label>
<input type="text" id="username" placeholder="username">
id is a unique name.

**Button Element**
<button>SUbmit </button>

type attribute
<button type="submit"> submit </button>
<button type="button"> do something </button>
<button type="reset"> do something </button>

Button using input
<input type="submit" >
‹input type= "submit" value="click me">

**NAME Attribute**

Name of the form control. Submitted with the form as part of a namelvalue pair.

<input type="text" placeholder= "enter name" id="username" name="username"/>

**CHECKBOX**

<input type= "checkbox" name="age" id="age" checked />
<label for="age"> I am 18+ </label>
